{
  "texts": [
    "This work tries to address the 'technology-education tension', comparing two different theoretical frameworks for interpreting how students' cognitive abilities are engaged in the use of technological devices.",
    "Since Pritchard (2014 Pritchard (, 2016)) arguably offers only a partial solution to the technology-education tension (TET), I propose a more encompassing solution that combines Fasoli's taxonomy of cognitive artifacts with Pritchard's framework of virtue epistemology.",
    "Thus, in Sect. 1.1 I will present Pritchard's framework of cognitive character and virtue epistemology applied to education.",
    "In Sect. 2, I will introduce Pritchard's solution to the technology-education tension, showing that it is only partial and confined to a limited set of cases (Sect.",
    "Then, I will try to offer a more encompassing framework for addressing the TET and the potential uses of ChatGPT in educational settings, by combining Pritchard's (2013 Pritchard's (, 2014 Pritchard's (, 2016)) framework of virtue epistemology with Fasoli's (2017 Fasoli's (, 2018)) taxonomy of cognitive artifacts."
  ]
}